			<image xml:id="corner-orientation" width="35%" source="./images/grey_cube.svg" /></statement>
			<solution>
				<p>The cubies affected by this move are <m>ufr</m> and <m>dbl</m>.
					This move reorients the affected cubies, and since the cubies are corners, it has order 3.
					Due to the effects on the <m>ufr</m> cubie, which has <m>fur</m> as an anagram, the name <term>Corner Bulldog</term> was suggested.
				</p>

			</solution>

			</exploration>

			
		<convention xml:id="middle-rotate">
			<p>
				By <m>M_R</m> we mean the clockwise rotation of the middle layer as you look at the right face of the Cube. That is, <m>M_R</m> rotates the middle layer parallel to <m>R</m>.
			</p>

		</convention>


		<heuristic xml:id="cube-move-er">
				<statement>
					Consider the following sequence of Cube moves:
					<me>
						\text{Three Edge Tango} = M_R^2 U^{-1} M_R^{-1} U^2 M_R U^{-1} M_R^2
					</me>
				</statement>
			</heuristic>
			
			<exploration>
