			<image xml:id="edge-rotation" width="35%" source="./images/grey_cube.svg" /></statement>
			<solution>
				<p>
					This moves cycles three edge cubies clockwise on the up face:
					<me>
						uf \to ul \to ur \to uf.
					</me>
					Since it's a cycle of three cubies, it has order 3.
					Following our name for <xref ref="cube-move-cr" />, we suggested the name <term>Three Edge Tango</term>.
					We also observed that if you reverse the direction of the upper rotations, you move the same three cubies, but in counterclockwise fashion.
					That is, the move
					<me>
						M_R^2 U M_R^{-1} U^2 M_R U M_R^2
					</me>
					moves 
					<me>
						uf \to ur \to ul \to uf.
					</me>
				</p>

			</solution>

